CONNECTED TV (CTV) ADVERTISING AGREEMENT
This Advertising Agreement ("Agreement") is entered into on this feb,14, 2026 (the "Effective Date") by and between: 
[Streaming Service Name/Publisher] ("Publisher"), with a principal address of [Disney],
AND
[Advertiser/Agency Name] ("Client"), with a principal address of [Nike]. 
1. SCOPE OF SERVICES
Publisher agrees to deliver advertising services for the Client across its streaming properties (the "Properties"). The specific, negotiated placements are outlined in Exhibit A (Insertion Order - IO). 
2. CTV CAMPAIGN SPECIFICATIONS (Exhibit A)
The following terms shall be defined in the IO:
Campaign Name: [Valentine day gifting for nike brand]
Term: [feb 9 2026] to [feb 14, 2026]
Inventory Type: [e.g., Premium/Direct/Programmatic PMP]
Targeting: [ Contextual relevant for valentine gifting season, Demographic for both male or female, Geo-targeting USA]
Impressions Goal: [10M impressions]
Price Model: [Fixed CPM $50 ($/1,000 impressions)]
Budget: [$2M]
Frequency Cap: [Max 5 views per user per day/week]
3. CREATIVE SUBMISSION AND SPECIFICATIONS
Delivery: Client shall deliver all advertisement assets in [Format, e.g., 1080p, VAST 4.0] at least [10] business days prior to the campaign start date.
Compliance: All ads must comply with current IAB standards for CTV and the legal, moral, and privacy requirements of the jurisdiction(s). 
4. PAYMENT TERMS
Invoicing: Publisher will invoice Client [Monthly/After Campaign] based on Publisher’s ad server reports.
Payment: Payments are due within 60 days of invoice receipt.
Late Fees: [Optional: 1% per month] interest on overdue payments. 
5. MEASUREMENT AND MAKEGOODS
Reporting: Publisher will provide daily/weekly reporting on impressions, completion rates (VCR), and Frequency.
Under-delivery: If the agreed-upon impression goal is not met, Publisher will provide a "makegood" in the form of additional ad placements at no cost to the Client, or issue a pro-rata credit.
Verification: Third-party verification for Impression tracking and Brand Safety (e.g., IAS, DoubleVerify) is [Accepted/Not Accepted]. 
6. WARRANTIES AND REPRESENTATIONS
Brand Safety: Publisher warrants that ads will not run next to content that is defamatory, obscene, or illegal.
Intellectual Property: Client warrants they own or have the rights to all content in the advertisement. 
7. TERMINATION
Either party may terminate this Agreement with [7] days’ written notice. In the event of breach, the non-breaching party may terminate with [7
] days’ notice if the breach is not cured. 
8. CONFIDENTIALITY
Both parties agree to maintain the confidentiality of pricing, audience data, and campaign performance metrics. 
